HEADWORD: Polysynthetic
<hw>Pol`y*syn*thet"ic</hw>
<pr>(p⟦ocr⟧l`⟦icr⟧*s⟦icr⟧n*th⟦ecr⟧t"⟦icr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Poly-</ets> + <ets>synthetic</ets>.]</ety> <def>Characterized
by polysynthesis; agglutinative.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Polysynthetic twinning</b></col> <fld>(Min.)</fld>,
<cd>repeated twinning, like that of the triclinic feldspar, producing
fine parallel bands in alternately reversed positions.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Polysyntheticism</ent>⟦br⟧
